# 🛠️ How Senior Engineers Prevent This

## ✅ 1. Crash Monitoring Tools

Use:

* Firebase Crashlytics
* Sentry

Track:

* Device
* OS version
* Stack trace
* App state (foreground/background)

---

## ✅ 2. Defensive Coding

* No force unwraps
* Safe indexing
* Graceful fallbacks

---

## ✅ 3. Background-safe architecture

* Use:

  * Background tasks API
  * Background URLSession
* Avoid:

  * Heavy processing

---

## ✅ 4. Thread safety

* Main thread → UI only
* Background → processing

---

## ✅ 5. Memory optimization

* NSCache
* Image resizing
* Pagination

---

## ✅ 6. Logging (VERY IMPORTANT)

Log:

* App state
* Thread
* API responses

---

# 🚨 Debug Checklist (Production)

When crash happens, ask:

* [ ] Was app in background?
* [ ] Any force unwrap?
* [ ] Any async thread issue?
* [ ] Large memory usage?
* [ ] API response mismatch?
* [ ] Background task expired?
* [ ] Core Data thread issue?

---

# 💡 Senior Insight

> Foreground crashes = your bug
> Background crashes = your architecture flaw

Because background requires:

* lifecycle awareness
* resource discipline
* strict threading

